      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: harden sync archive creation",
        "body": "## Summary\n- replace local `tar --null -T -` archive creation with a shared Go tar/gzip writer\n- route provider and Windows sync archive creation through the shared helper\n- add regression coverage for option-looking filenames such as `--checkpoint=1`\n\n## Security\nSeveral sync paths built archives by feeding repository filenames to local `tar` through `--files-from`. On tar implementations that parse files-from entries as options, a repository file whose name starts with `--` can be interpreted as a tar flag instead of archived as data. Building the archive in Go removes that filename-as-option class and avoids depending on local tar behavior.\n\n## Verification\n- `go test ./...`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `rg -n \"exec\\\\.CommandContext\\\\([^\\\\n]*\\\\\\\"tar\\\\\\\"|--null\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"-T\\\\\\\"|--null.*-T\" internal/cli internal/providers -S`\n",
        "branch": "codex/secure-env-profile",
